6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both ShortlyAI and Wordtune share a solid foundation of core features including Short Form. Where ShortlyAI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Long Form, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Wordtune uniquely offers Tone Control and Multilingual and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, ShortlyAI holds an overall score of 5/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Wordtune scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Wordtune comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while ShortlyAI begins at $79/mo. Wordtune stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. ShortlyAI requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
