a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. ShortlyAI is best suited for blog posts, long form articles, stories, distraction free writing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Wordtune, meanwhile, shines for rewriting, tone adjustment, non native English speakers, academic writing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, ShortlyAI describes itself as \"Distraction-free AI writing tool focused on long-form content.\" Wordtune, established in 2018, positions itself as \"AI rewriting tool that helps you say exactly what you mean.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Wordtune** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0), more features (4 vs 2), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean ShortlyAI is a poor choice — far from it. ShortlyAI excels in its own right, particularly for blog posts and long form articles.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class sentence rewriting and rephrasing, go with Wordtune. If clean distraction-free interface matters more to you, ShortlyAI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
